                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 17: Bandel Thermal Power project and three other coal-based energy producers will get $225 million from the World Bank to improve efficiency. The International Bank for Reconstruction and Development will give a $180-million loan while the Global Environment Facility will grant $45.4 million.                             
	 Mumbai, Dec. 17: Moodys today upgraded the long-term foreign currency deposit ratings of 14 domestic lenders, including the State Bank and ICICI Bank. The rating has been upgraded to Ba1 from Ba2.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 17: PNBs cheap home loan scheme will also be available on loans above Rs 30 lakh and up to Rs 50 lakh. The bank charges 8.5 per cent for fixed loans for three years. Subsequently, the rate will be linked to the PLR.
                                                                                                                          
